Create the Dataset

Now that you updated the metadata file with the predicate, you can create the dataset.

Required Editions and User Permissions
Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

User Permissions Needed
To upload a CSV and metadata file: Upload External Data to CRM Analytics

Warning: Perform steps in non-production environment to avoid impacting other datasets.

Create the dataset by following these steps:
Go to the home page in CRM Analytics.
Click Create | Dataset.
Click CSV.
Select the CSV file and metadata (schema) file.
Enter "SalesTarget" as the dataset name.
Choose an app to store the dataset.
Click Create Dataset.
CRM Analytics confirms upload success and creates a job to create the dataset.

Verify the job completes successfully by following these steps:
Click the gear icon and select Data Monitor.
Refresh Jobs button to view latest statuses.
